1.Connecting mysql db to python
    1. pip install mysql-connector-python
    2. https://dev.mysql.com/doc/connector-python/en/connector-python-example-connecting.html
    3. For querying products
        https://dev.mysql.com/doc/connector-python/en/connector-python-example-cursor-select.html

2. Create a Backend File -
    This performs certain function like add product, show product and delete products
    This file is linked to MySQL DB so it directly append the changes into that database


3. Create a Flask Server to link the frontend with the python code for local server
    Create routines in Flask file like /getProducts, /addProduct, /deleteProduct
    Use the connection to the SQL method to link to the server
    Jsonify the files i.e convert the response into JSON file
    Add "ACCESS CONTROL ALLOW ORIGIN" which is the course policy

4. Build the UI and call these methods - VSCode
    HTML - skeleton of the UI
    CSS - Color and feel of the UI
    JS - this file connects all the backend and frontend (ui) by making calls to the server and backend